milestones.description: Sangakkara has become the top scorer for ASIA in ODIs with 120 runs, going past Rahul Dravid's 75
Sehwag has broken the record for most sixes (2) in ODIs for ASIA, going past Shoaib Akhtar's 1
Sangakkara has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (42) in an innings in ODIs for ASIA, going past Sehwag's 26
Steve Tikolo has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (30) in an innings in ODIs for AFR, going past Prince's 20
Heath Streak has conceded the most runs in an innings (64) in ODIs for AFR, going past Kallis's record of 42
Mahela Jayawardene has broken the record for most catches (4) in ODIs for ASIA, going past Ashish Nehra's 1
Mahela Jayawardene has broken the record for most catches in an innings (4) in ODIs for ASIA, going past Chaminda Vaas's 1
Sehwag and Sangakkara's 91-run partnership is ASIA's highest for the 2nd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 17 between Ganguly and Sehwag
Mahela Jayawardene and Mohammad Yousuf's 79-run partnership is ASIA's highest for the 4th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 7 between Rahul Dravid and Mohammad Yousuf
Inzamam-ul-Haq and Zaheer Khan's 32-run partnership is ASIA's highest for the 8th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 17 between Abdul Razzaq and Zaheer Khan
Dippenaar and de Villiers's 27-run partnership is AFR's highest for the 2nd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 5 between Kallis and Dippenaar
Justin Kemp and de Villiers's 46-run partnership is AFR's highest for the 5th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 4 between Steve Tikolo and Prince
Shaun Pollock and Steve Tikolo's 38-run partnership is AFR's highest for the 7th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 11 between Shaun Pollock and Prince
Heath Streak and Shaun Pollock's 42-run partnership is AFR's highest for the 9th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 10 between Prince and Justin Kemp
Inzamam-ul-Haq has broken the record for most ODIs (2) as captain for ASIA, going past Ganguly
Abdul Razzaq has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (3) for ASIA, going past Zaheer Khan
Nicky Boje has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (2) for AFR, going past Mark Boucher
This is the highest match aggregate (517) involving teams Asia XI & Africa XI in ODIs
Sehwag and Sangakkara's 91-run partnership is ASIA's highest for any wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 59 between Sehwag and Jayasuriya
